## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Execution Profile Decision**: The autonomous agent loop introduces a "broader control surface" as you described. For development/testing, the `individual` profile with `dev` environment will be used with relaxed governance. For production deployment, should the autonomous loop require explicit approval for every computer-use action, or should it operate within a configurable autonomy budget (e.g., 50 actions per hour)?

> [!WARNING]
> **Security Surface Expansion**: Enabling direct command execution from the dashboard creates a new attack vector. The plan includes allowlist/denylist, Guardian oversight, and audit logging. Please confirm this approach is acceptable for the individual profile during development.

> [!IMPORTANT]  
> **LLM Provider for Autonomous Loop**: The autonomous agent loop needs an LLM to reason about goals and select actions. During development, this will use the configured provider from Settings (default: Ollama `gemma3:1b`). For production autonomy, should we enforce a minimum model tier (e.g., Tier 3+ models only)?

