## Enhancement Suggestions

> [!TIP]
> **Accessibility-First Browser Perception**: Instead of relying solely on screenshots + vision models for browser automation, use Playwright's `page.accessibility.snapshot()` as the primary perception layer. This is dramatically cheaper (no vision model needed), faster, and more reliable. Fall back to screenshots only when the accessibility tree is insufficient (e.g., canvas-heavy pages).

> [!TIP]
> **Structured Command Categories**: For the computer command execution panel, pre-define categories of commands (system info, network diagnostics, file management, process management, development tools) with safe defaults. This provides a safer starting surface than raw shell access.

> [!TIP]
> **Telemetry Retention Tiers**: Not all telemetry needs to persist forever. Implement a tiered retention policy:
> - **Hot** (in-memory, 1 hour): Full detail, all events
> - **Warm** (SQLite, 7 days): Summarized, significant events
> - **Cold** (file export, 90 days): Aggregated metrics, policy decisions
> This prevents the `prism-activity.db` from growing unboundedly.

> [!TIP]
> **Goal Templates for Autonomous Operation**: Pre-define common autonomous goals as templates (e.g., "Research topic X and summarize findings", "Monitor webpage Y and alert on changes", "Run test suite and report results"). This provides safe entry points for autonomous behavior.

> [!TIP]
> **Dual-Channel Logging**: The Logs & Debug tab should support both a human-readable rendered view and a raw JSON view (toggle). The raw JSON view is what Guardian and other LLM agents consume. The rendered view is for the human operator. Both views show the same data with different presentations.

